info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued September 25 at 1:59AM EDT by NWS Miami
info.description: ...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern Palm Beach County through 245 AM EDT... At 159 AM EDT, National Weather Service meteorologists were tracking strong thunderstorms along a line extending from Lion Country Safari Park to 8 miles east of Lantana. Movement was northeast at 35 mph. HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... West Palm Beach, Boynton Beach, Wellington, Jupiter, Palm Beach Gardens, Lake Worth, Riviera Beach, Palm Beach, Tequesta, Juno Beach, Greenacres, Royal Palm Beach, Palm Springs, North Palm Beach, Lantana, Lake Park, Atlantis, Haverhill, Cloud Lake, and Palm Beach International Airport. MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH
info.instruction: These winds can down small tree limbs and branches, and blow around unsecured small objects. Seek shelter in a safe building until the storm passes.
